In Bitkoin, all nodes in the network are simultaneously book holders, auditors, currency issuers, buyers and sellers.
How does this network work?
Each transaction between two users actually occurs between two e-mail addresses, like an e-mail.
Only for each new payment can the user choose another address, thus ensuring anonymity.
A set of information related to this transaction is electronically signed using a double-key encryption system.
